description:
## What
1. Endpoint type URIs: document the 4 new well-known types added in current spec:
   - urn:jmap:chat:cap:calendar-event
   - urn:jmap:chat:cap:availability
   - urn:jmap:chat:cap:task
   - urn:jmap:chat:cap:filenode
   No code change needed (type is String, extensible) — but add constants:
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_VTC: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:vtc';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_PAYMENT: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:payment';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_BLOB: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:blob';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_CALENDAR_EVENT: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:calendar-event';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_AVAILABILITY: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:availability';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_TASK: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:task';
   pub const ENDPOINT_TYPE_FILENODE: &str = 'urn:jmap:chat:cap:filenode';

2. Add WebSocket message types (new module: src/wss.rs or src/websocket.rs):
   - ChatStreamEnable { data_types: Vec<String>, chat_ids: Option<Vec<String>>, contact_ids: Option<Vec<String>> }
   - ChatStreamDisable {}
   - ChatTypingEvent { chat_id: String, sender_id: String, typing: bool }
   - ChatPresenceEvent { contact_id: String, presence: String, last_active_at: Option<UTCDate>, status_text: Option<serde_json::Value>, status_emoji: Option<serde_json::Value> }
   - WssClientMessage enum: StreamEnable(ChatStreamEnable), StreamDisable(ChatStreamDisable)
   - WssServerEvent enum: TypingEvent(ChatTypingEvent), PresenceEvent(ChatPresenceEvent), Unknown

   Serialization: @type field for all (serde tag)

## Tests
Fixture tests/fixtures/wss/chat_stream_enable.json
Fixture tests/fixtures/wss/chat_typing_event.json
Fixture tests/fixtures/wss/chat_presence_event.json
Assert: all round-trip against hand-written fixtures from spec examples
Assert: unknown @type in WssServerEvent deserializes to Unknown variant (not error)
